                <h2>Ways To Get Best Rates On Flights</h2>

                <p>Getting yourself a good rate on your flight of choice would require some skills. These skills will always ensure you the best deals. So here is how to find cheap flights-</p>
                <ol>
                    <li><b>Book during your destination’s low seasons-</b> Booking during low seasons will always ensure you cheaper tickets for your flights. Due to the lesser traffic, the flight ticket is also kept at a much more affordable rate. Research which season is considered to be the low season of your desired travel destination that you are flying to.</li>
                    <li><b>Choose low-cost airlines-</b> Choosing low-cost airline flights will ensure that you pay a very affordable airfare to begin with. If you research well then you can book yourself seats on a low-cost airline that provides all the standard services and even some extra perks.</li>
                    <li><b>Book your flight very last minute-</b> Often during the last few hours airlines choose to lower their seat prices to be sold out. Booking during this time would be affordable. This is a very risky method for one to book through.</li>
                    <li><b>Check a low fare calendar –</b> This is similar to the first trick the only difference being is the lowering of the fare is on a day-to-day basis instead of it being based on seasons. Through this, you can easily book even during the peak seasons by checking which date of that season will have a more affordable price.</li>
                    <li><b>Being flexible with dates-</b> For all the tips of a cheap flight it is most integral that your dates are flexible and so is your time. Having more flexible dates increases to chance of getting the best price for your ideal flight ticket.</li>
                    <li><b>Getting your booking done early –</b> If you book early you will get some early selection discounts. This is a very safe method to get a good deal. Not only that you will also get a better and flexible selection of seats if you book way early.</li>
                    <li><b>Use the miles you have collected so far-</b> Make good use of all the miles that you have collected so far for your next flight booking getting great discounts. This along with many other priority perks makes having miles worth it.</li>
                    <li><b>Use a good third-party booking interface-</b> Using a good third-party booking interface is actually very integral in getting good deals. There are websites such as Faresmatch which has the flight comparison website feature. In this feature, you can compare the best fare price of your flight on different websites at this one place.</li>
                    <li><b>Using Airline Credit Cards-</b> Using credit cards introduced by certain airline companies to book their airline flights will help one get great discounts. Not only that you will also get good and free entry into special airport lounges with these cards.</li>
                    <li><b>Book connecting flights-</b> Often when you book connecting flights or one with longer layovers your overall trip becomes less expensive. Booking yourself for good connecting flights must be done after doing much research. Even with this tip, one would have to be very flexible with their travel dates and their travel times.</li>
                </ol>
                <h2>Some Tips On How To Never Miss A Flight</h2>

                <p>Now that you have booked your ideal flight, you mustn't miss your flight at any cost. Here are some tips to follow to never miss your flight-</p>
                <ol>
                    <li><b>Time your travel very well-</b> If you are not timing your travel well you will have a lot of problems. It is necessary that you plan your travel to the airport, the check-in time, and everything very precisely. Timing everything well will ensure that you never miss a flight.</li>
                    <li><b>Stay near the airport –</b> If you live somewhere way far away from the airport then it might be a problem. To avoid any sort of trouble it will be a good idea to stay in a dorm or hotel near the airport. In this way, you will reach the airport right on time and never miss the flight.</li>
                    <li><b>Check In Online –</b> Checking in the traditional way at the airport would take a lot of time and might result in you missing your flight. It is rather smart if one would just do their check-in online through a mobile app or the official website of the chosen flight airline company.</li>
                    <li><b>Pack Appropriately –</b> Often due to carrying the wrong things one would be held down at security and lose their flight. So please pack very appropriately when you are flying so you do not have to miss your flight while being interrogated by airport security.</li>
                </ol>
